# Code of conduct of the collaborator's agreement

## Our commitment

We, as members, contributors, and leaders, are committed to participating in our
community a harassment-free experience for everyone, regardless of age, body
size, visible or invisible disability, ethnicity, sexual characteristics, gender
identity and expression, level of experience, education, socioeconomic status,
nationality, personal appearance, race, religion or sexual identity
and orientation.

We are committed to acting and interacting in ways that contribute to an open, welcoming,
diverse, inclusive and healthy community.

## Our standards

Examples of behavior that contribute to a positive environment for our
community includes:

* Show empathy and kindness towards other people.
* Respect different opinions, points of view and experiences.
* Gracefully give and accept constructive feedback
* Accept responsibility and apologize to those affected by our mistakes,
  and learning from experience
* Focus on what is best not only for us as individuals, but also for
  community in general

Examples of unacceptable behavior include:

* The use of sexualized language or images and attention or
  advances of any kind
* Funny, insulting or derogatory comments and personal or political attacks.
* Public or private harassment
* Post private information of others, such as an email or physical
  address, without your explicit permission
* Other conduct that could reasonably be considered inappropriate in a
  professional environment

## Execution responsibilities

Community leaders are responsible for clarifying and enforcing our standards of
acceptable behavior and will take appropriate and fair corrective action in
response to any behavior that they consider inappropriate, threatening, offensive,
or harmful.

Community leaders have the right and responsibility to delete, edit, or reject
comments, commits, code, wiki edits, issues, and other contributions that are
is not aligned with this Code of Conduct, and will communicate the reasons for moderation
decisions when appropriate.

## Scope

This Code of Conduct applies in all community spaces and also applies when
an individual officially represents the community in public spaces.
Examples of representation of our community include the use of an official email address,
post through an official social media account, or act as a designee
representative at an online or offline event.

## Execution

Cases of abusive, harassing, or unacceptable behavior can be
informed the community leaders responsible for the application in
info@smistoken.com.
All complaints will be reviewed and investigated promptly and fairly.

All community leaders are required to respect the privacy and security of the
reporter of any incident.

## Application guidelines

Community leaders will follow these Community Impact Guidelines to determine
the consequences of any action that they consider to be in violation of this Code of Conduct:

### 1. Correction

** Community Impact **: Use of Inappropriate Language or Other Considerate Behavior
unprofessional or unpleasant in the community.

** Consequence **: A private written warning from community leaders, providing
clarity about the nature of the offense and an explanation of why
the behavior was inappropriate. A public apology can be requested.

### 2. Warning

** Community Impact **: One violation through a single incident or series
of actions.

** Consequence **: A warning with consequences for continued behavior. No
interaction with the persons involved, including unsolicited interaction with
those that enforce the Code of Conduct, for a specified period of time. This
includes avoiding interactions in community spaces, as well as external channels
like social media. Violation of these terms may result in a
permanent ban.

### 3. Temporary ban

** Community Impact ** - A serious violation of community standards, including
sustained inappropriate behavior.

** Consequence **: a temporary ban on any type of interaction or public
communication with the community for a specified period of time. I do not post or
private interaction with the people involved, including unsolicited interaction
with those who enforce the Code of Conduct, it is allowed during this period.
Violation of these terms may lead to a permanent ban.

### 4. Permanent ban

** Community Impact **: Demonstrate a pattern of community violation.
